<h3>Credits</h3>

<p>
The editors express their gratitude to the developers of the Valency Patterns
Leipzig Online Database, Hans-Jörg Bibiko, Alexander Jahraus, and Robert
Forkel. It is primarily due to them that this has become such a very special
product, fulfilling all our wishes and going far beyond.
</p>

<p>
Next we are grateful to our funders: <strong>(i)</strong> the Deutsche
Forschungsgemeinschaft
(${h.external_link('http://www.dfg.de/', 'DFG')})
for providing crucial funding based on the DFG-funded Forschergruppe
${h.external_link('http://www.uni-leipzig.de/~va/', '"Grammatik und Verarbeitung verbaler Argumente"')}
over a period of 3 years
(2010–2013). And <strong>(ii)</strong> we acknowledge the
<a href="http://www.mpg.de/en">Max Planck Society</a>,
